Beautifully executed meal especially given the size of our table!  The wait staff was on queue every time.  Our drinks were never empty, water was always filled and the wine was always being poured.  Excellent service!  As for the food, I'm not a huge meat eater so I decided to forego the whole reason behind this restaurant and opt for 1lb. of King Crab legs and then munch on a few bites of steak from other plates in our party.  My legs were quite substantial, however they got cold fast since they come split in 1/2.  Not a bit deal, but when you're paying $45 for a plate of food you'd like it to be warm.  I also had the chance to taste the New York Strip and Ribeye, both cooked to perfection, nice and tender.  Our table decided to order several sides to share including the asparagus, mac and cheese and something else that escapes my memory (too many bottles of wine).  All the sides were absolutely amazing and the asparagus was cooked perfectly.  Great experience eating at Gallaghers and I would certainly recommend it to anyone.  Know before you go:  the bathrooms are a mile away so don't drink too much!!

